        <div n="262-0852" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-262-0852-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-262-0852-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-262-0852-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-262-0852-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-262-0852-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-262-0852-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-262-0852-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-262-0852-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-262-0852-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-262-0852-line-1"><hi rend="display-initial">A</hi> BARD on whom <hi rend="underline">Ph<unclear>oe</unclear>bus</hi> his Spirit bestow'd</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-262-0852-line-2"> Resolving t'acknowledge the Bounty he ow'd,</l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-262-0852-line-3"> Found out a new Method at once of confessing,</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-262-0852-line-4"> And making the most of so mighty a Blessing;</l><l n="5" xml:id="spp-262-0852-line-5"> To the God he'd be grateful, but Mortals he'd chouse,</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-262-0852-line-6"> By making his Patron preside in his House,</l><l n="7" xml:id="spp-262-0852-line-7"> And wisely foresaw his Advantage from thence,</l><l n="8" xml:id="spp-262-0852-line-8"> That the God wou'd in Honour bear most of th' Expence:</l><l n="9" xml:id="spp-262-0852-line-9"> So, the Bard he finds Drink, and leaves <hi rend="underline">Ph<unclear>oe</unclear>bus</hi> to treat</l><l n="10" xml:id="spp-262-0852-line-10"> With the Thoughts he inspires, regardless of Meat.</l><l n="11" xml:id="spp-262-0852-line-11"> Hence they that come hither expecting to dine,</l><l n="12" xml:id="spp-262-0852-line-12"> Are always fobb'd off with sheer Wit and sheer Wine.262-0852   </l></lg></div>
      </div>
